Thank you for choosing Law Offices of Johnson & Partners to represent you in connection with your personal injury claim resulting from the automobile accident on March 15, 2025. This letter outlines the terms of our engagement and professional relationship.

## 1. SCOPE OF SERVICES

We will provide the following legal services:
Legal representation regarding your personal injury claim, including settlement negotiations, filing of necessary court documents, and representation in court proceedings if required.

This engagement does not cover any other matters not specifically described above. If you require legal services beyond this scope, we will need to discuss and agree upon the terms for those additional services.

## 2. FEES AND EXPENSES

**Fee Structure:** Contingency fee of 33% of any settlement or judgment obtained
**Hourly Rates:** Not applicable for contingency cases
**Retainer:** No initial retainer required for contingency cases

In addition to professional fees, you will be responsible for expenses incurred on your behalf, including but not limited to filing fees, court costs, expert witness fees, travel expenses, copying charges, and other reasonable out-of-pocket expenses.

## 3. BILLING AND PAYMENT

We will send you monthly invoices detailing the services rendered and expenses incurred. Payment is due within 30 days of receipt. We reserve the right to withdraw from representation if invoices remain unpaid after 60 days.

## 4. CONFIDENTIALITY

All information related to your representation will be kept confidential in accordance with the rules of professional responsibility governing attorneys. We cannot disclose confidential information without your consent except as required by law or ethics rules.

## 5. TERMINATION

You may terminate our services at any time by providing written notice. We may withdraw from representation as permitted by the applicable rules of professional conduct. Upon termination, you will remain responsible for any fees and expenses incurred prior to termination.

## 6. FILE RETENTION

We will maintain your file for 7 years after the conclusion of this matter, after which we may dispose of it without further notice.

## 7. AGREEMENT

If these terms are acceptable, please sign and return a copy of this letter. Your signature will constitute your acceptance of these terms and authorization to proceed.

